## Quick Reference

### Creating a New Feature

1. **Define schema** (if needed):

   ```typescript
   // src/lib/server/db/schema.ts
   export const myTable = pgTable('my_table', { ... });
   ```

2. **Create remote functions**:

   ```typescript
   // src/routes/my-feature/data.remote.ts
   import { query, command } from "$app/server";
   ```

3. **Create page**:

   ```svelte
   <!-- src/routes/[[lang=lang]]/my-feature/+page.svelte -->
   <script lang="ts">
   	import { page } from '$app/state';
   	import { t } from '$lib/i18n/index.svelte';
   	import { getData } from './data.remote';

   	const language = $derived((page.params?.lang || 'ro') as 'ro' | 'en');
   </script>

   <h1>{t('my-feature.title') || 'My Feature'}</h1>
   ```

4. **Add authentication** (if needed):

   ```typescript
   // In remote function using getRequestEvent()
   import { getRequestEvent } from "$app/server";
   import { redirect } from "@sveltejs/kit";

   export const getProtectedData = query(async () => {
     const { locals } = getRequestEvent();
     if (!locals.user) throw redirect(302, "/login");
     // Use locals.user...
   });
   ```

### Common Patterns

**Protected Route:**

```typescript
export const load: PageServerLoad = async (event) => {
  if (!event.locals.user) throw redirect(302, "/login");
  return { user: event.locals.user };
};
```

**Form Submission with Remote Function:**

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import { createItem } from './data.remote';

	let name = $state('');
	let loading = $state(false);

	async function handleSubmit() {
		loading = true;
		try {
			await createItem({ name });
			name = '';
		} finally {
			loading = false;
		}
	}
</script>

<form
	onsubmit={(e) => {
		e.preventDefault();
		handleSubmit();
	}}
>
	<input bind:value={name} />
	<button type="submit" disabled={loading}>Submit</button>
</form>
```

**Database Query:**

```typescript
const result = await db
  .select()
  .from(table.myTable)
  .where(eq(table.myTable.id, id));
```

